# ScholarAI — Complete Implementation Plan

> **Status:** ✅ Understanding Lock Confirmed — Ready for Implementation  
> **Date:** 2026-03-14  
> **Team:** 3 developers · 16 weeks  
> **Architecture:** Modular Monolith

---

## Confirmed Decisions (from Brainstorming)

| # | Question | Decision |
|---|---|---|
| Q1 | Embedding dimension | **Migrate schema to 384-dim** (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) |
| Q2 | LLM backend | **Gemini API** (free tier; OpenAI as fallback) |
| Q3 | Mentorship module | **Deferred** — not in MVP |
| Q4 | Interview simulator | **Voice-enabled** — Whisper STT + Gemini response |
| Q5 | Scraper targets | **DAAD, scholarship.com, Fulbright, scholarships.ca** |
| A6 | Synthetic data | **Regeneratable** — CLI script with seed parameter |
| A7 | Human trust experiment | **60 students** (not 30) |
| A8 | Development approach | **Approach A — Phased Modular Monolith** ✅ |

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dependency on Gemini API key** — The interview and RAG modules require a `GOOGLE_API_KEY`. This must be provisioned before Phase 3 begins. Store it in Docker secrets or [.env](file:///c:/Users/Admin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/scholarai-platform/.env).

> [!WARNING]
> **Voice (Whisper) adds infra requirement** — Whisper runs locally. Ensure the Docker host has ~2GB RAM headroom for the `openai-whisper` base model. CPU inference is acceptable for FYP demo.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Schema migration is destructive** — Changing `VECTOR(768)` → `VECTOR(384)` requires an Alembic migration that drops and recreates affected columns. Any existing vector data will be lost. Back up before running.

