### Component 1: Database Schema Migration

#### [MODIFY] [database_schema.md](file:///c:/Users/Admin/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/scholarai-platform/docs/database_schema.md)
- Change all `VECTOR(768)` columns to `VECTOR(384)`
- Remove `mentors` table (deferred)
- Add `eligibility_requirements` table (per spec)
- Add `html_snapshots` table (scraper debug storage)
- Add `audit_logs` table (admin operations)

#### [NEW] Alembic migration file: `backend/alembic/versions/001_init_schema.py`
- `CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector`
- Create all confirmed tables
- HNSW indexes using `vector_cosine_ops` on 384-dim columns

**Tables (final confirmed list):**

```
users                   — id, email, password_hash, role, created_at
student_profiles        — id, user_id, citizenship, gpa, ielts_score,
                          research_score, volunteer_score, target_field,
                          target_country, degree_level, profile_embedding VECTOR(384)
universities            — id, name, country, ranking
programs                — id, university_id, name, field_of_study, degree_level
scholarships            — id, name, provider, country, degree_level,
                          field_of_study, min_gpa, deadline, full_description,
                          source_url, is_active, scholarship_embedding VECTOR(384)
eligibility_requirements — id, scholarship_id, requirement_type, value
applications            — id, student_id, scholarship_id, status,
                          ai_match_score, shap_explanation JSONB, applied_at
documents               — id, student_id, application_id, document_type,
                          storage_url, content_embedding VECTOR(384), uploaded_at
html_snapshots          — id, source_url, html_content TEXT, scraped_at, job_id
audit_logs              — id, admin_id, action, target_table, target_id,
                          old_value JSONB, new_value JSONB, created_at
embedding_cache         — id, text_hash, embedding VECTOR(384), created_at
```

