### Component 4: Data Ingestion Pipeline

#### [NEW] Scraper design per target

| Target | URL | Method | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| DAAD | daad.de/en/scholarships | Playwright (JS-rendered) | Rate limit: 1 req/5s |
| Fulbright | fulbright.org | Playwright | Robots.txt compliant |
| scholarships.ca | scholarships.ca | requests + BeautifulSoup fallback | Simpler HTML |
| scholarship.com | scholarship.com | Playwright | Pagination required |

**Pipeline per source:**
```
robots.txt check
  → skip if disallowed
  → HTML retrieval (Playwright headless)
  → DOM parsing (CSS selector → XPath fallback)
  → Pydantic schema validation
  → Duplicate detection (url hash)
  → Insert to scholarships table
  → Save html_snapshots record
  → Queue embedding_task (async Celery)
```

**Schedule:** Celery Beat — weekly per source  
**Monitoring:** Flower dashboard at `:5555`

---

### Component 5: ML Training Pipeline

```
data/synthetic_vN.csv
    │
    ▼
feature_engineering.py
    → gpa_normalized, research_score, language_score,
       program_match_score, volunteer_score
    │
    ▼
trainer.py
    → XGBoost classifier
    → 80/10/10 train/val/test split (stratified)
    → Hyperparameter sweep: mlflow.autolog()
    → Log: dataset_version, feature_version, hyperparams,
            precision@5, recall@5, ndcg@5, mrr
    │
    ▼
MLflow Model Registry
    → Stage: Staging → Production
    │
    ▼
explainer.py
    → SHAP TreeExplainer (per prediction)
    → LIME TabularExplainer (per prediction)
    → Store shap_explanation JSONB in applications table
```

**Benchmark framework (3 models):**

| Model | Components |
|---|---|
| Model A | Stage 1 only (graph eligibility filter) |
| Model B | Stage 1 + Stage 2 (+ vector similarity) |
| Model C | Stage 1 + Stage 2 + Stage 3 (+ ML reranking) |

**Metrics:** Precision@5, Precision@10, Recall@5, Recall@10, NDCG@5, NDCG@10, MRR  
**Ablation:** Each stage removed independently, metrics re-evaluated

---

### Component 6: Knowledge Graph (Neo4j)

**Sync job:** `sync_postgres_to_neo4j` — Celery Beat, daily

```cypher
-- Node creation on sync:
MERGE (s:Student {id: $id}) SET s += {gpa: $gpa, citizenship: $citizenship}
MERGE (sc:Scholarship {id: $id}) SET sc += {name: $name, min_gpa: $min_gpa}
MERGE (u:University {id: $id}) SET u += {name: $name}
MERGE (er:EligibilityRequirement {id: $id})

-- Relationships:
MERGE (s)-[:ELIGIBLE_FOR]->(sc)   -- when gpa >= min_gpa AND citizenship matches
MERGE (u)-[:OFFERS]->(p:Program)
MERGE (p)-[:FUNDED_BY]->(sc)
MERGE (sc)-[:REQUIRES]->(er)
```

