## Decision Log (Final)

| ID | Decision | Alternatives | Reason |
|---|---|---|---|
| D1 | Modular monolith | Microservices | 3 devs, 16 weeks |
| D2 | PostgreSQL + pgvector 384-dim | Qdrant, Chroma | Single DB; HNSW production-grade; matches all-MiniLM-L6-v2 |
| D3 | Gemini API (gemini-1.5-flash) | OpenAI GPT-4o, Ollama | Free tier available; avoids cost; generous rate limits |
| D4 | Whisper base (local) | Deepgram, AssemblyAI | No API cost; offline capable; sufficient quality |
| D5 | Celery + Redis | APScheduler, Dramatiq | Priority queues + DLQ + Flower monitoring |
| D6 | MLflow | W&B, DVC | Self-hostable; no account needed; native XGBoost support |
| D7 | SHAP + LIME both | SHAP only | Two XAI methods = stronger academic contribution |
| D8 | Mentorship module deferred | Include in MVP | Scope risk; adds auth/privacy complexity with no ML value |
| D9 | Synthetic data regeneratable | Generated once | Reproducibility + ablation study requires multiple seeds |
| D10 | 60 students for trust experiment | 30 | Increased statistical power (user decision) |
| D11 | Scraper targets: DAAD, Fulbright, scholarships.ca, scholarship.com | Broader web crawl | Controlled, curated, robots.txt compliant starting set |
